(15. LLMs and almost good code) Tj
T*
(Source: Entropic Thoughts | Published: Tue, 09 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0200) Tj
T*
(Link: https://entropicthoughts.com/llms-and-almost-good-code) Tj
T*
(TL;DR: My new prior is that top-of-the-line LLMs working on easy tasks generate code that is) Tj
T*
(maybe 10 % more complicated than necessary. I also think we accept this complexity too easily,) Tj
T*
(because it comes from code that is right here , right now , solving an immediate problem. This) Tj
T*
(may have consequences for maintenance in the long term. The background to this discovery was) Tj
T*
(that I needed to do some CRUD plumbing in a work project. It was a simple change that mostly) Tj
T*
(mirrored existing functionality. This is a perfect fit for LLMs, in my experience, so I used a) Tj
T*
(frontier model to generate the code for it. The change ended up being a total of just over 200) Tj
T*
(lines, mostly additions. The part of the generated code we?ll talk about is a 24-line function) Tj
T*
(that converts an arbitrary \(user-supplied\) string to a safe HTTP header value. \(Continue) Tj
T*
(reading the full article on the web.\)) Tj
T*
