(running by Haruki Murakami \(thanks for the recommendation, Rishi\) and a line stuck out to me:) Tj
T*
(Perhaps I'm just too painstaking a type of person, but I can't grasp much of anything without) Tj
T*
(putting down my thoughts in writing. This line resonated with me because I've also found that) Tj
T*
(the best way for me to understand a concept or idea is for me to write about it. Reading only) Tj
T*
(gets me so far. The act of articulating what is stored in my brain into something legible and) Tj
T*
(understandable is thinking and understanding. I worry about the education system, which has had) Tj
T*
(the entire concept of writing as a form of study upended by AI, and universities have seen) Tj
T*
(their first decline in literacy and comprehension ever recorded. But this isn't what this post) Tj
T*
(is about, this post is about remembering things. I have often received complements from friends) Tj
T*
(and strangers alike on how good my memory is. This tends to be complime...) Tj
